# RULE 04 — LOCKED INVARIANTS

These invariants are non-negotiable. Every block MUST enforce them. Violations are blocked at PR review and CI.

## Database invariants

- **`operating_company_id` RLS** — every table touched must have RLS scoped to operating company
- **All views** must use `WITH (security_invoker = true)` — never SQL SECURITY DEFINER
- **Lockstep INSERT pattern** for atomic transactions involving multiple tables
- **Append-only audit events** on every mutation (insert/update/state-change)
- **Permanent records** — void records, never `DELETE FROM`. Use `voided_at` + `voided_by` columns.
- **Migrations idempotent** — use `DO $$ BEGIN ... END $$;` blocks with `IF NOT EXISTS` guards
- **Cache from `master_data.drivers` NEVER used in render path** (Part 4.5.4.2 of formal blueprint) — render path must always read from canonical source
- **Single-link constraint** per WF-012 — one bank txn maps to one entity link
- **Single-factor invariant** per WF-017 — only one active factor per company; partial unique index + trigger raising `E_FACTOR_MULTIPLE_ACTIVE`

## API + frontend invariants

- **Display IDs server-generated only** — never composed in frontend, never user-editable
- **Production NEVER serves fake data** — all fixture/seed data fallbacks must be env-gated (e.g., `if (NODE_ENV !== 'production')`)
- **Primary buttons:** `+ Create` or `+ Book` — NEVER `+ New`, NEVER `+ Add`
- **Operating company switcher** must be respected in every module — RLS + UI filter

## Workflow invariants (LOCKED)

- **WF-038** — HOS violation block on driver assignment
- **WF-044** — Maintenance-due advisory warning on dispatch
- **WF-050** — DVIR major defect → `is_dispatch_blocked = true` hard block
- **WF-053** — cross-module posting service config
- **WF-064** — Manager high-risk action notifies Owner

## 425C invariant

Virtual banks (Factoring · Escrow) EXCLUDED from main bank totals on lines 19-23 of Form 425C per UST guidance. This is a Ch.11 DIP regulatory requirement.

## Enforcement

- `db:verify:*` scripts validate database invariants
- `npm run verify:arch-design` validates UI tab counts (CI gate)
- PR template checklist requires explicit acknowledgment of invariant compliance
